cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal logic and winning conditions in games.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with two-player games and winning strategies.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses complexity results for determining the winner in different types of games.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with strategies and winning conditions in games, which are relevant to AI.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of classical variants of games to solve games with costs, which involves programming and implementation.
